<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-35-0810 </DOCNO><TEXT>Although the probability of causation approach is the only scientificbasis on which a given cancer can be judged to be causally related toa given exposure, the impact of this concept on the radiation safetyprogram could be counter-productive. As health physicists, the practicesand the concepts we employ have been developed to protect the worker.Effective dose equivalent and committed dose equivalent are protectiveconcepts but useless for probability of causation analysis. Perhaps extensiverecords will be the only way that good radiation protection and probabilityof causation analysis can coexist.</TEXT></DOC>